<p>For his article <a href="https://doi.org/10.1093/mind/fzae061">&#8220;A Universal Money Pump for the Myopic, Naive, and Minimally Sophisticated,&#8221;</a> in the April 2025 issue of <em>Mind</em>, philosopher Johan Gustafsson devised this minimal paradoxical stairway to illustrate a cyclic ranking: A appears higher than B, B appears higher than C, and C appears higher than A.</p>
<p>Two other perplexities, while we&#8217;re at it &#8212; by Mike Tolleb:</p>
